docs.abstract: Central locations and spacious warehouse areas make older postal facilities, like those in Chicago and New York, tantalizing candidates for transformation.
docs.snippet: Central locations and spacious warehouse areas make older postal facilities, like those in Chicago and New York, tantalizing candidates for transformation.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Postal Service moved out of its longtime main post office in downtown Chicago in 1997, but ideas for remaking the Art Deco behemoth never gained traction. The huge building sat vacant, a far cry from the time when workers could sort up to 35 million letters a day there and residents posted mail in its elegant lobby, an airy space with stone floors and decorative panels.

headline.main: As Work Space, Old Post Offices Have a Timeless Allure
headline.print_headline: As Work Space, Old Post Offices Have a Timeless Allure

docs.abstract: The company, one of the biggest marketers in the U.S., hasn’t returned to the platform because of concerns that its ads could appear with offensive content.
docs.snippet: The company, one of the biggest marketers in the U.S., hasn’t returned to the platform because of concerns that its ads could appear with offensive content.
docs.lead_paragraph: AT&T, one of the nation’s biggest marketers, has yet to return to YouTube nearly a year after pulling its advertising from the platform because of concerns that it could appear alongside offensive material.

headline.main: YouTube Revamped Its Ad System. AT&T Still Hasn’t Returned.
headline.print_headline: Offensive Content Drove Big Advertisers Off YouTube. AT&T Still Isn’t Back.

docs.abstract: Gaps remained between Canada, Mexico and the United States as the sixth round of talks over the future of the North American Free Trade Agreement concluded.
docs.snippet: Gaps remained between Canada, Mexico and the United States as the sixth round of talks over the future of the North American Free Trade Agreement concluded.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTREAL — Discussions to revamp the North American Free Trade Agreement moved from stalemate to actual negotiation during the sixth round of talks that concluded on Monday, but a deal was still far from guaranteed as Mexico, Canada and the United States continue to squabble over how to reshape the 24-year-old pact.

headline.main: Signs of Progress in Nafta Talks but Countries Remain Deeply Divided
headline.print_headline: Not Close to Deal on Nafta, but Not in a Stalemate, Either

docs.abstract: In the next few weeks, you will see fewer viral videos and news articles from media companies, and instead see more posts that include interactions between you and the people you know.
docs.snippet: In the next few weeks, you will see fewer viral videos and news articles from media companies, and instead see more posts that include interactions between you and the people you know.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook has introduced sweeping changes to the kinds of posts, videos and photos that its more than two billion members will see most often, saying on Thursday that it would prioritize what their friends and family share and comment on while de-emphasizing content from publishers and brands.

headline.main: Facebook Overhauls News Feed to Focus on What Friends and Family Share
headline.print_headline: Facebook Feed Shifting Focus To Genial Ties

docs.abstract: The British designer will replace Kris Van Assche and show his first collection in June. His appointment comes two months after his surprise departure from Louis Vuitton.
docs.snippet: The British designer will replace Kris Van Assche and show his first collection in June. His appointment comes two months after his surprise departure from Louis Vuitton.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The British designer Kim Jones was confirmed as the new artistic director of Dior Homme on Monday, two months after he stepped down as artistic director of men’s wear at Louis Vuitton. He will replace Kris Van Assche, who was in the role 11 years.

headline.main: Dior Confirms Kim Jones as Men’s Wear Artistic Director
headline.print_headline: Artistic Director Joins Dior After Leaving Louis Vuitton
